### 1. Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 2. Sign up a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "testuser",
    "email": "test@example.com",
    "password": "password123",
    "dailyCalorieGoal": 2000
}

### 3. Login
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "test@example.com",
    "password": "password123"
}

### 4. Search food from OpenFoodFacts
GET {{baseUrl}}/food/search?q=chicken
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Add a meal entry (returns the new entry ID)
POST {{baseUrl}}/meals
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
    "date": "2026-05-13",
    "mealType": "Breakfast",
    "foodName": "Oatmeal",
    "calories": 350,
    "carbs": 55.0,
    "protein": 12.0,
    "fat": 6.0
}

### 6. Add another meal entry for testing deletion
POST {{baseUrl}}/meals
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
    "date": "2026-05-13",
    "mealType": "Lunch",
    "foodName": "Chicken Salad",
    "calories": 450,
    "carbs": 20.0,
    "protein": 35.0,
    "fat": 25.0
}

### 7. Get daily summary (check the "id" field on each item)
GET {{baseUrl}}/meals/daily?date=2026-05-13
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 8. Delete a meal entry (replace with actual UUID from response above)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/meals/REPLACE_WITH_ACTUAL_ID
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 9. Try deleting with a fake/non-existent ID to see the bug
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/meals/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
